fRf45o", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/ThreadAnnotation.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e4216d8898360c2e573bd412e966b956462338d6", "parents": ["c287079aaf7f3f61f04cc8ab12df91d661371d97"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1458016: Fix bad cast to Text. r=bz\n\nI think it's harmless security-wise, since Text and char data are both\nnsIContent, so the vtable offset should be the same.\n\nI could also just do AsContent(), which may be cleaner but involve a virtual\ncall, or add AsCharacterData(), just let me know.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 79I9CuCmioF", "files": ["dom/base/Selection.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c0f3401afe5bcaf18f71d17e25f3719d8fdfd00", "parents": ["e4216d8898360c2e573bd412e966b956462338d6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dustin J. Mitchell \u003cdustin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1458105 - try more to fetch automationrelevance; r=gps\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LdcGes2mf01", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/files_changed.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6f975a367b79036dc280c04677b33678aec38af0", "parents": ["4c0f3401afe5bcaf18f71d17e25f3719d8fdfd00"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Shal \u003cmshal@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1455799 - Make an explicit webidl export target; r=bz,chmanchester\n\nBy including codegen.pp and having a target for codegen.pp, we were\nrelying on make to build out-of-date include files and re-exec itself\nafter they are built. However, make produces an error if the file does\nnot exist, which is why this include was changed to a -include in bug\n1378965. Unfortunately this means that make ignores not only a\nnon-existent file, but also any errors in regenerating the target from\nthe webidl py_action.\n\nInstead we can make a separate stub file target for webidl generation,\nand include the codegen.pp that's generated as a side-effect of the\npy_action. This way make will fail properly if the webidl generation\nfails, and there is no error message about a missing codegen.pp on the\nfirst build.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GjB8zDuMfnL", "files": ["dom/bindings/Makefile.in", "dom/bindings/mozwebidlcodegen/__init__.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "359cecde7c3ea604dc7f55ae958b9de420924f44", "parents": ["6f975a367b79036dc280c04677b33678aec38af0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1455745: Remove more accessibility related diagnostic crashes on Nightly. r=aklotz\n\nThis condition is rare and does indicate a problem which breaks accessibility.\nHowever, we aren't getting any closer to diagnosing this as a result of this crash, so it causes user pain without any gain to us.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GacAQDbhB0h", "files": ["accessible/generic/DocAccessible.cpp", "accessible/ipc/win/COMPtrTypes.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c36098a8e83f0238196d0bfbaad1f81ae84ae28e", "parents": ["359cecde7c3ea604dc7f55ae958b9de420924f44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1457802 part 1 - Remove nsCSSProps::GetColorName which is unused. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GybpTh6GYYx", "files": ["layout/style/nsCSSProps.cpp", "layout/style/nsCSSProps.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0bd3f2f95b5534428500314d70b273f2b6cb488f", "parents": ["c36098a8e83f0238196d0bfbaad1f81ae84ae28e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1457802 part 2 - Remove pref callbacks touching keyword tables from nsLayoutUtils. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8ZTyx9es772", "files": ["layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp", "layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3347987c7a8ac8eb9070c1a9ac88f146dd696668", "parents": ["0bd3f2f95b5534428500314d70b273f2b6cb488