"704d7726335d570bbffad5590ed15711444e9bab", "parents": ["573f3fb78bf774aa24fe0efb6975ca248529bbad"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\ncs -\u003e bb004f464a3f\nes-CL -\u003e e9653d4318c1\nes-MX -\u003e f8a219da9089\nfi -\u003e 3518823932f5\nfr -\u003e 0c89e92b70c4\nia -\u003e b4c52bca36b7\nmai -\u003e 964f0135bebd\nnl -\u003e 98758b79d929\nru -\u003e bffbc735e8f7\nsr -\u003e 293ca9a97334\nth -\u003e 4a6a8ceb458f", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7850d199832dc83f7f270184f2f2987423df43fa", "parents": ["704d7726335d570bbffad5590ed15711444e9bab"], "tags": []}], "date": 1526199808, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9216": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 09749108da2b\nes-ES -\u003e bbfbf45a934d\nes-MX -\u003e 7da12be652ea\nfi -\u003e fe4f02edf1a5\nhy-AM -\u003e e2fa1c0d0917\nne-NP -\u003e b501f6b7748d\npt-PT -\u003e 5944e2331079\nzh-CN -\u003e e73d39ca7cb5", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "733efce852e4686847c00bc71739ba79ad880d1f", "parents": ["7850d199832dc83f7f270184f2f2987423df43fa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 2e092f8581b6\nes-CL -\u003e 59a84f040aea\nes-ES -\u003e c395f3c07245\nfi -\u003e 88bb4c95b679\nhy-AM -\u003e f40683e7c548\nit -\u003e 51b39753a3b3\nne-NP -\u003e e5e4c50ad7f9\npt-PT -\u003e 5944e2331079\nzh-CN -\u003e e73d39ca7cb5", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f39d016977d883cd42b1288d1382571ffd6c9156", "parents": ["733efce852e4686847c00bc71739ba79ad880d1f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1526235728, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9217": {"changesets": [{"author": "Narcis Beleuzu \u003cnbeleuzu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1456807 - Disable browser_taskbar_preview.js for frequent failures. r=jmaher, a=test-only", "files": ["browser/modules/test/browser/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d09efd7ece67d78ac7dd8194adb26c9cd214fb6c", "parents": ["f39d016977d883cd42b1288d1382571ffd6c9156"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 962248 - Rewrite zoom test to be less terrible. r=dthayer, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ByUM61fsOgh", "files": ["browser/components/customizableui/test/browser_934951_zoom_in_toolbar.js", "browser/components/customizableui/test/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f32dcbc07c2063c28459b845f800d3420957606", "parents": ["d09efd7ece67d78ac7dd8194adb26c9cd214fb6c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1461092 - Unship GetPropertyCSSValue in Firefox 61. r=xidorn, a=RyanVM", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b81ec88ad0975d85f189e3ce88aa1db241cba1f", "parents": ["2f32dcbc07c2063c28459b845f800d3420957606"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Stephen A Pohl \u003cspohl.mozilla.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1446900 - Place bug 1348361 (async content process launching) behind an ifdef and disable it to avoid numerous top crashers. r=jld, a=RyanVM", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp", "ipc/glue/GeckoChildProcessHost.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "768ac7426e6cd6d500f49dc1e15ff9119cb4cf24", "parents": ["8b81ec88ad0975d85f189e3ce88aa1db241cba1f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1458166 - Clear out tracks while destroying MediaStream. r=bryce, a=RyanVM\n\nMediaStream::Destroy() is part of a controlled shutdown sequence.\nIf there are still tracks with content beyond Destroy() they will\nonly get caught by the dtor, which may be on CC shutdown and too late.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GV6XRiTCIRk", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3da1d132f3832a77bcd8bdd6d68e6f151aba5764", "parents": ["768ac7426e6cd6d500f49dc1e15ff9119cb4cf24"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1458166 - Remove listeners before destroying MediaStreams. r=bryce, a=RyanVM\n\nIf listeners are still registered to a MediaStream on MediaStream::Destroy\n(triggered by MediaStream::UnregisterUser below), they will catch and act\non further events from the MediaStream (such as a track ending).\n\nThis may dispatch runnables that are unnecessary since we know we are\nshutting down.\n\nIf we first remove the listeners from the MediaStream we will never see\nsaid events.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IZ1kENqL2C8", "files": ["dom/media/DOMMediaStream.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8ed61558ac0256d0304f45784eb76250418849ba", "parents": ["3da1d132f3832a77bcd8bdd6d68e6f151aba5764"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1458720 - Make RunOnAllContentParents runnable from any thread. r=Ehsan, r=jcj, a=RyanVM\n\nIn bug 1215723 RunOnAllContentParents was added to the DataStorage\nimplementation so we could make more security state information available in\nchild processes. It uses IPC APIs, which in general are not thread-safe. We need\nto make sure that these APIs are only accessed on the main thread, which means\nwe have to copy any necessary data, create a runnable, and send it to the main\nthread to do the actual work. Note that the IPC APIs are async, so this dispatch\ncan be async as well.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HwkgSX1iORU", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/DataStorage.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "47f7391d2bb0cdfea0cd05c91ed30a2fc067f6ee", "parents": ["8ed61558ac0256d0304f45784eb76250418849ba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kyle Machulis \u003ckyle@nonpolynomial.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1436241 - Check redirect status code before forwarding to NPAPI. r=jimm, r=pauljt, a=RyanVM\n\nNPAPI may handle a 307 redirect across different origins, while they\nshould only happen on same origin requests. Have the browser check\nthis before forwarding to NPAPI.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5vxMooygI4g", "files": ["dom/plugins/base/nsPluginStreamListenerPeer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7002b1d37d0ce38568466a46f20ce425c2c7a8a6", "parents": ["47f7391d2bb0cdfea0cd05c91ed30a2fc067f6ee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "k88hudson \u003ck88hudson@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1460119 - gSnippetsMap.getTotalBookmarksCount() never resolves. r=Mardak, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Dx4tkHTb4zz", "files": ["browser/extensions/activity-stream/lib/SnippetsFeed.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "43bcbb69db2123e46600f7fa93842f87b70c977a", "parents": ["7002b1d37d0ce38568466a46f20ce425c2c7a8a6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1526239127, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9218": {"changesets": [{"author": "Peter Van der Beken \u003cpeterv@propagandism.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1453951 - Crash in non-virtual thunk to nsInProcessTabChildGlobal::WrapObject. r=bz, a=RyanVM\n\nWe need to call nsInProcessTabChildGlobal::Init immediately after creating the\nnsInProcessTabChildGlobal, so that we set up the binding object eagerly. Otherwise we\nmight end up calling WrapObject on it.", "files": ["dom/base/nsFrameLoader.cpp", "dom/base/nsInProcessTabChildGlobal.cpp", "dom/base/nsInProcessTabChildGlobal.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e4115e95bc3179250ac2f4293a531ce406d7710", "parents": ["43bcbb69db2123e46600f7fa93842f87b70c977a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Schuster \u003cevilpies@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1459607 - CallSiteObjects can only contain strings. r=jandem, a=abillings", "files": ["js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "453294133297be02ae10459bf4e430ba1df039a0", "parents": ["2e4115e95bc3179250ac2f4293a531ce406d7710"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1451262 - Call NS_ProcessPendingEvents after StopSSLServerCertVerificationThreads. r=mayhemer, a=RyanVM\n\nIf there are still pending events after we null out gSocketThread, OnSocketThread() will always return false, which can trigger assertions.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CovFIU3cKL", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsSocketTransportService2.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "720baaffac8cf0b71e351720bc3617a508d039d1", "parents": ["453294133297be02ae10459bf4e430ba1df039a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Stenberg \u003cdaniel@haxx.se\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1452436 - Callback when resolving a host already in progress. r=mcmanus, a=RyanVM\n\nIf a callback has already been called for the hostrecord, it is\npartially resolved already by TRR so the new callback should be called\nat once.", "files": ["netwerk/dns/nsHostResolver.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1da8d36ce5a4c6f41863ecd4edd5b0ae5c548c69", "parents": ["720baaffac8cf0b71e351720bc3617a508d039d1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1460636 - Don't trace jsids on ObjectGroup in the cycle collector. r=jonco, r=sfink, a=RyanVM\n\nFor some reason, the CC spends a lot of time tracing jsids on\nObjectGroups when an addon is installed. This patch avoids that by\nadding a canSkipJsids flag to JSTracer, and using it in\nObjectGroup::traceChildren. If this is true, then the tracer is free\nto not report every jsid. This flag is set to true for the two CC\ntracers.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CWFqQEr0SxV", "files": ["js/public/TracingAPI.h", "js/src/gc/Marking.cpp", "xpcom/base/CycleCollectedJSRuntime.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b8ada24da4ddc1a1b3961f9d0fffa7fd75f95c3", "parents": ["1da8d36ce5a4c6f41863ecd4edd5b0ae5c548c69"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1459697 - Part 1: In EllipseShapeInfo distance field calculation, remove a warning that might trigger due to rounding error, and shorten the iteration of each block pixel row, when possible. r=dbaron, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6itpj3HBSRy", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFloatManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c2cc19eb1159bea5cd8e8be6c2c9c5fd41e7b053", "parents": ["7b8ada24da4ddc1a1b3961f9d0fffa7fd75f95c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1459697 - Part 2: Account for the possibility that EllipseShapeInfo may not generate an interval for the entire BStart() to BEnd() range, due to rounding error in the distance field calculation. r=dbaron, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CYeBKhDYD1F\n\nThe distance field does not calculate a true Euclidean distance, so it is\nunreasonable to require that the intervals span all of the BStart() to BEnd()\nfloat area. The final block pixel may not generate an interval at all due to\nrounding errors. This change makes accomodation for the rounding errors and\nadds asserts to ensure we aren't tolerating errors outside the area of the\nlast block pixel.", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFloatManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b6cde02169dc497ff43e489b92686f441dcd1a3b", "parents": ["c2cc19eb1159bea5cd8e8be6c2c9c5fd41e7b053"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1459697 - Part 3: Add a crashtest. r=dbaron, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GrUrVIdzO6", "files": ["layout/generic/crashtests/1459697.html", "layout/generic/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9bbd3253d3a5600576f454155f1da7dc83e2a483", "parents": ["b6cde02169dc497ff43e489b92686f441dcd1a3b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1459697 - Part 4: Change a WPT reftest to make failures visible in red. r=dbaron, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: A4UxNn4Njpi\n\nThis test applied a green color to the test area, when it should be\ntransparent, to allow the red to show through in case of test failure. Without\nthis change, this test won't catch cases where the float area is too small.", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-shapes/shape-outside/supported-shapes/inset/shape-outside-inset-029.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5fcefe47c777376011b67be862e45bbb62e85d48", "parents": ["9bbd3253d3a5600576f454155f1da7dc83e2a483"], "tags": []}], "date": 1526241381, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9219": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\naz -\u003e 21e45fef93f6\nbs -\u003e fe107048ce04\nfr -\u003e 6045e58dd394\nms -\u003e fdf6fc23b6c9\npt-PT -\u003e 6be6a7c58d38\nsv-SE -\u003e 603d6a57ba80", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4fc88b50a6d4a61a66ade901b88ad92ab2f5ec2e", "parents": 