illa Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e\"", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging d81b581fbd2cdb5fcfd982c7d2d3222204192725 with FIREFOX_61_0b9_BUILD1, FIREFOX_61_0b9_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "654f6404195eff0b8c577a49809505d6c240c0a7", "parents": ["b346efcb9279b5837e9c12a33b529a677cdbeb12"], "tags": []}], "date": 1527606097, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9279": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1457703 - Fix count of compacting update tasks started. r=sfink, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/gc/GC.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53adb415c14201960a2bdae4dcd18ecb3700c636", "parents": ["654f6404195eff0b8c577a49809505d6c240c0a7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1457703 - Use function pointers rather than virtual run method for GC parallel tasks. r=sfink, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/gc/Allocator.cpp", "js/src/gc/GC.cpp", "js/src/gc/GCParallelTask.h", "js/src/gc/GCRuntime.h", "js/src/gc/Nursery.cpp", "js/src/gc/Statistics.h", "js/src/vm/HelperThreads.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f8717a7f5b16f1c77ae46839df6c10ef261baeb", "parents": ["53adb415c14201960a2bdae4dcd18ecb3700c636"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1456451 - [CSD] Update toplevel GdkWindow property when it's recreated at nsWindow::SetDrawsInTitlebar(). r=jhorak, a=RyanVM\n\nImplement SetCompositorHint() which sets _NET_WM_BYPASS_COMPOSITOR GtkWindow property when it's recreated\nat nsWindow::SetDrawsInTitlebar().\n\nWindow role/class is handled by nsWindow::RefreshWindowClass(), it uses stored window class\npassed to nsWindow::SetWindowClass().\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1JJsK1ZQyvu", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "982e4bff688adbae25274a9f0aca6f288f3fa8e5", "parents": ["1f8717a7f5b16f1c77ae46839df6c10ef261baeb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Odvarko \u003codvarko@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1462882 - Avoid NPE when filtering using remote-ip. r=jryans, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IJ2lNgMRCYz", "files": ["devtools/client/netmonitor/src/utils/filter-text-utils.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d44d4c2a178ffb0af2860fa6a0b7c2640828260d", "parents": ["982e4bff688adbae25274a9f0aca6f288f3fa8e5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J.C. Jones \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1463170 - Set AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.userHandle to null. r=ttaubert, r=smaug, a=RyanVM\n\nSummary:\nThe WebAuthn spec says to set `AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.userHandle` to\nnull when the authenticator returns no user handle (e.g., when allowList is set),\nbut we return an empty ArrayBuffer. This is because of the defaults in\nAuthenticatorAssertionResponse.h, as the field is itself unset.\n\nWe missed this change to the spec that happened in December [2], so this also\nhas a corresponding WebIDL update. I don't see any other instances of WebIDL\ndifferences.\n\n[1] https://w3c.github.io/webauthn/#ref-for-dom-authenticatorassertionresponse-userhandle%E2%91%A0\n[2] https://github.com/w3c/webauthn/commit/3b2a1d141cbd8f2954f073a6b6598d954398a986\n\nTest Plan: https://treeherder.mozilla.org/#/jobs?repo=try&revision=59a2ab255ef14e935c1aa9f457276f8e61e5d779\n\nReviewers: smaug, ttaubert\n\nBug #: 1463170\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D1337", "files": ["dom/webauthn/AuthenticatorAssertionResponse.cpp", "dom/webauthn/tests/test_webauthn_loopback.html", "dom/webidl/WebAuthentication.webidl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "36c03b72db500ae707a6876cc34c811a639d1ad7", "parents": ["d44d4c2a178ffb0af2860fa6a0b7c2640828260d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jed Davis \u003cjld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1461546 - Extend SANDBOX_HAS_USER_NAMESPACES telemetry and make it opt-out. r=chutten, a=RyanVM\n\nThis is opt-out telemetry because the prerelease channels aren't\nrepresentative of the larger population.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FI576NAS8Ss", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2cd2229ebfa625c21597e77c0866f2a326ffa743", "parents": ["36c03b72db500ae707a6876cc34c811a639d1ad7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1461324 - Check for closing for-of iterators before closing a for-in one. r=arai, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/jit/JitFrames.cpp", "js/src/vm/Interpreter.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7e502b527f07efa658bd26c60240daa4a604931a", "parents": ["2cd2229ebfa625c21597e77c0866f2a326ffa743"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1450688. r=bz, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4KHNpxiziWd", "files": ["dom/xbl/nsXBLBinding.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5a428c9953abbbac43fb43a9c4e424630a760dee", "parents": ["7e502b527f07efa658bd26c60240daa4a604931a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1456975 - Check fields in nsMozIconURI deserialization. r=agaynor, a=RyanVM", "files": ["image/decoders/icon/nsIconURI.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d31a2ab994fd49bf2641540ee38354c183f5ab9b", "parents": ["5a428c9953abbbac43fb43a9c4e424630a760dee"], "tags": []}], "date": 1527631338, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9280": {"changesets": [{"author": "abhinav \u003cabhinav.koppula@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1462886 - Fix for filter flag breaking the netmonitor when using invalid values. r=Honza, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5cvUX2sb7k0", "files": ["devtools/client/netmonitor/src/utils/filter-text-utils.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_filter-flags.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "267ac0403602e61866090391cac76bfe89becea1", "parents": ["d31a2ab994fd49bf2641540ee38354c183f5ab9b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1461977 - sync tree's scrollTop with scroll state when tree scrollTop value changes outside of user scroll. r=nchevobbe, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4aIX9mSkg1T", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/components/VirtualizedTree.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/test/mochitest/chrome.ini", "devtools/client/shared/components/test/mochitest/test_tree_13.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5e583b4b75c6c5c9e3ada88505d0eb1cdc874022", "parents": ["267ac0403602e61866090391cac76bfe89becea1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1450607 - P1. Fix constness. r=gerald, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CeftB0qmzTf", "files": ["dom/media/MediaCache.cpp", "dom/media/MediaCache.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83e5c99c142fe675abc35b6a5118f84161f50331", "parents": ["5e583b4b75c6c5c9e3ada88505d0eb1cdc874022"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1450607 - P2. Synchronously seek to prepare for resuming following stop request. r=gerald, a=RyanVM\n\nBug 1415090 attempted to remove the need to access from the MediaResource members of MediaCacheStream from the main thread.\nHowever, by doing so the logic flow for resuming the channel changed from a synchronous access to an asynchronous one.\nThis changed some assumptions and allowed the ChannelMediaResource to be used before the Seek call completed.\n\nFor now, re-add a cross thread access to the MediaCacheStream. A more elegant fix will be worked on in bug 1464045\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2xBTjDEqrkI", "files": ["dom/media/ChannelMediaResource.cpp", "dom/media/MediaCache.cpp", "dom/media/MediaCache.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "befed261c0ec350c1420b44f752ab603c757147e", "parents": ["83e5c99c142fe675abc35b6a5118f84161f50331"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1450607 - P3. Remove unused argument. r=gerald, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6NU9BLJi6kl", "files": ["dom/media/ChannelMediaResource.cpp", "dom/media/MediaCache.cpp", "dom/media/MediaCache.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ccf0bb5b140d41cc8f17d7bffe854d7ccee5a3b1", "parents": ["befed261c0ec350c1420b44f752ab603c757147e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1463884 - Part 1: Move methods only used by fontconfig backend from gfxPlatformFontList to the fontconfig subclass. (No functional change.) r=emilio, a=RyanVM", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxPlatformFontList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4fcab7ec6dd04b57b9b10ec367e35f7961fb10d2", "parents": ["ccf0bb5b140d41cc8f17d7bffe854d7ccee5a3b1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1463884 - Part 2: Remove always-true argument aCheckEnvironment from gfxFcPlatformFontList::GetSampleLangForGroup. r=emilio, a=RyanVM", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "27f627cf78833ee91ae2958cf3a58c806e2d835c", "parents": ["4fcab7ec6dd04b57b9b10ec367e35f7961fb10d2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1463884 - Part 3: Make gfxFcPlatformFontList::TryLangForGroup safe for off-main-thread use when called from GetSystemFontList. r=emilio, a=RyanVM", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a3142138b6c90f43e76ab7508b32aa931a589616", "parents": ["27f627cf78833ee91ae2958cf3a58c806e2d835c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1527631875, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9281": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changesets 1f8717a7f5b1 and 53adb415c142 for static analysis failures.", "files": ["js/src/gc/Allocator.cpp", "js/src/gc/GC.cpp", "js/src/gc/GCParallelTask.h", "js/src/gc/GCRuntime.h", "js/src/gc/Nursery.cpp", "js/src/gc/Statistics.h", "js/src/vm/HelperThreads.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6ca43a4c43d080317a667c3f92f62b5eee686b4b", "parents": ["a3142138b6c90f43e76ab7508b32aa931a589616"], "tags": []}], "date": 1527632915, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9282": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nick Thomas \u003cnthomas@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1462120 - Update verify fixes for ESR60 branch, r=bhearsum a=release  DONTBUILD", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-update-verify-config/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-update-verify/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/update_verify_config.py", "testing/mozharness/scripts/release/update-verify-config-creator.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0c6274aa49006fbc6170b8d0f355b8eb84dec09c", "parents": ["6ca43a4c43d080317a667c3f92f62b5eee686b4b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1527636746, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "nthomas@mozilla.com"}, "9283": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "